Merge pull request #229 from ejfinneran/fix-catch-all

Catch-all method firing for all messages

Fix catch-all

The 'break if message.done' line was causing the results array to be
populated by false no matter what the listener#call returned.  This
caused the catch-all hook to trigger even if a previous listener had
handled the message.

Also fixes some of the existing tests.

Robot constructor takes an extra argument now.

Fixes tests.
